name: The Complete Teacher Anchor™
description:
The Teacher Anchor™ is a binder system that serves to keep you organized and intentional in the classroom. Named "The anchor" as a symbol of hope and steadfastness – two words that any teacher could use to describe her journey each school year. When an anchor is raised on a ship, it signifies that a new journey has begun. Inside your Teacher Anchor™ is 120 pages full of lesson plans, classroom organizers, curricular checklists, Common Core standards and big idea planners, substitute teacher notes, and a student data section that includes master forms and checklists for gathering pre/post test data, running records, small groups, individual conferencing and more! Your Teacher Anchor™ includes: • Heavy duty leatherette, silver foil stamped binder • 2" D-ring spine in the standard three-hole size • The Classroom Planning Sheet Set with blank lesson plan pages, year-at-a glance pages, birthday celebration planner, volunteer forms, substitute teacher notes, school event forms, and plenty of space for personal reflection. • The Student Data Sheet set composed of individual and small group data master forms for you to use as needed. Forms include pre/post test data, Running Records, small group, individual student conferences and blank weekly and monthly lesson planning pages for your small group work only. Don't forget to visit the Teacher Anchor™ Free Printable library where you can download Common Core checklists, schedulers, organizers, and much more to outfit your Teacher Anchor!

For more information, please visit The Teacher Anchor Page © C. Jayne Teach 2013 *THANK YOU to Teasley Photography for all of the product image shots seen throughout the shop.
